1
00:00:44,419 --> 00:00:47,255
I don't want any complications
in our plans.

2
00:00:47,338 --> 00:00:49,424
<i>Mikoy Pinagpala,</i>

3
00:00:49,507 --> 00:00:52,177
<i>I finally found you!</i>

4
00:00:52,260 --> 00:00:54,512
You might do something you'll regret.

5
00:00:54,596 --> 00:00:56,347
If anyone should regret something,

6
00:00:56,431 --> 00:00:58,016
it’s that Czech Viktor guy!

7
00:00:58,099 --> 00:01:00,143
If you really want to get back at him,

8
00:01:00,226 --> 00:01:01,561
don't kill me.

9
00:01:02,187 --> 00:01:03,104
Because the truth is,

10
00:01:03,188 --> 00:01:05,023
I can help you.

11
00:01:09,611 --> 00:01:10,487
Hello?

12
00:01:10,570 --> 00:01:11,446
Hello?

13
00:01:11,529 --> 00:01:13,490
Honestly, I didn't expect you to call.

14
00:01:13,573 --> 00:01:14,991
I really want to see you.

15
00:01:15,075 --> 00:01:17,202
And bring a burger, okay?

16
00:01:17,285 --> 00:01:19,162
<i>And extra fries.</i>

17
00:01:19,245 --> 00:01:20,288
<i>Mikoy is in trouble.</i>

18
00:01:20,371 --> 00:01:21,873
<i>He just gave us a distress signal.</i>

19
00:01:34,803 --> 00:01:38,056
<i>Hide and seek under the bright moon</i>

20
00:01:38,932 --> 00:01:40,433
<i>Not at the back</i>

21
00:01:40,517 --> 00:01:42,560
<i>Not in front</i>

22
00:01:42,644 --> 00:01:44,521
<i>Not at the back</i>

23
00:01:44,604 --> 00:01:46,272
<i>On the count of three</i>

24
00:01:46,356 --> 00:01:48,441
<i>You’re already hiding, bro!</i>

25
00:01:48,525 --> 00:01:50,193
<i>Not below</i>

26
00:01:50,276 --> 00:01:52,445
<i>Not above</i>

27
00:01:52,529 --> 00:01:53,530
Got you!

28
00:02:02,914 --> 00:02:03,957
My dear,

29
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:05,583
is everything okay?

30
00:02:09,129 --> 00:02:10,630
He's probably swamped

31
00:02:10,713 --> 00:02:14,050
with everything he needs
to handle at the office.

32
00:02:16,094 --> 00:02:18,263
I just wanted to check if he's okay.

33
00:02:18,847 --> 00:02:22,725
You know, and I know,
that we need to protect him.

34
00:02:22,809 --> 00:02:25,395
Don't worry, dear. Okay?

35
00:02:25,478 --> 00:02:28,189
No one will disturb Mikoy anymore.

36
00:02:28,273 --> 00:02:30,066
I've handled it.

37
00:02:34,946 --> 00:02:38,658
And I don’t want him to get involved
with our plans here in the Philippines.

38
00:02:46,875 --> 00:02:48,293
You know that.

39
00:02:50,962 --> 00:02:54,591
But will he accept who you are?

40
00:03:08,646 --> 00:03:10,315
Funny boy!

41
00:03:10,899 --> 00:03:13,234
Where are you, funny boy?

42
00:03:13,776 --> 00:03:16,404
No one gets left behind, funny boy!

43
00:03:18,031 --> 00:03:19,532
Funny boy!

44
00:03:19,616 --> 00:03:21,326
Mikoy!

45
00:03:21,409 --> 00:03:23,661
I know you're here!

46
00:03:24,245 --> 00:03:26,789
You can't get away from me!

47
00:03:27,373 --> 00:03:29,000
Pinagpala!

48
00:03:30,543 --> 00:03:32,962
Mr. Pinagpala!

49
00:03:33,588 --> 00:03:35,298
Mikoy!

50
00:03:38,426 --> 00:03:39,886
Pinagpala!

51
00:03:54,651 --> 00:03:55,693
Pinagpala!

52
00:03:56,945 --> 00:04:00,240
Looks like you've got nowhere else to run!

53
00:04:01,491 --> 00:04:03,993
This is the end for you!

54
00:04:05,119 --> 00:04:05,954
Mikoy!

55
00:04:06,621 --> 00:04:08,581
You’re caught but not jailed.

56
00:04:08,665 --> 00:04:10,500
Because you're dead ball!

57
00:04:10,583 --> 00:04:12,835
Please, please…

58
00:04:26,474 --> 00:04:29,102
Agent Alex! Thank you, Lord!

59
00:04:30,395 --> 00:04:31,229
Go ahead.

60
00:04:31,312 --> 00:04:33,189
Give me a reason to finish you.

61
00:04:37,777 --> 00:04:39,445
All right, boys. Cuff him.

62
00:04:43,741 --> 00:04:45,034
Are you okay?

63
00:04:45,702 --> 00:04:47,787
- Are you sure you weren’t hit?
- Nothing.

64
00:04:48,413 --> 00:04:50,081
Wait, let me check first just in case.

65
00:04:50,164 --> 00:04:51,165
Here?

66
00:04:52,041 --> 00:04:54,210
- Okay.
- Hey. Wait.

67
00:04:54,294 --> 00:04:55,586
- Are you sure you’re not in pain?
- Yes.

68
00:04:55,670 --> 00:04:58,589
- You didn't get hit?
- Yes! Stop. You’re tickling me.

69
00:04:59,632 --> 00:05:01,801
I'm just making sure you're not hurt.

70
00:05:02,427 --> 00:05:03,803
I'm fine.

71
00:05:05,054 --> 00:05:06,556
- I didn’t get hit.
- Agent Alex!

72
00:05:10,768 --> 00:05:12,145
Yes, Bok.

73
00:05:16,607 --> 00:05:17,817
Stand him up.

74
00:05:17,900 --> 00:05:19,152
Thank you.

75
00:05:49,140 --> 00:05:50,349
- Mom!
- Hi!

76
00:05:50,433 --> 00:05:51,726
- Dad!
- Chiara!

77
00:05:51,809 --> 00:05:53,144
Is Mikoy here?

78
00:05:53,644 --> 00:05:55,104
Why? Isn't he with you?

79
00:05:56,022 --> 00:05:59,275
Maybe he's just working overtime.
Or maybe he just got stuck in traffic.

80
00:05:59,358 --> 00:06:03,529
Just relax first.
Would you like something to drink?

81
00:06:04,113 --> 00:06:07,825
Just wait. Tess is preparing
something for dinner.

82
00:06:09,368 --> 00:06:11,079
I'll just help with the cooking.

83
00:06:11,162 --> 00:06:12,705
Oh, no, don’t bother.

84
00:06:12,789 --> 00:06:14,290
You might get haggard. Just stay there.

85
00:06:14,373 --> 00:06:15,500
No, it's okay.

86
00:06:15,583 --> 00:06:18,002
I'm good at slicing.

87
00:06:18,586 --> 00:06:19,921
Oh, are you sure?

88
00:06:20,004 --> 00:06:21,255
All right then, here.

89
00:06:21,339 --> 00:06:22,840
Here, if you want.

90
00:06:22,924 --> 00:06:24,300
Just be careful, okay?

91
00:06:25,384 --> 00:06:27,929
Chiara, thank you so much
for your invitation

92
00:06:28,012 --> 00:06:30,139
to stay here for a few days.

93
00:06:30,223 --> 00:06:32,016
As for Betchay,

94
00:06:32,100 --> 00:06:33,184
he is going back to Cebu,

95
00:06:33,267 --> 00:06:35,645
so someone can watch
over our little bakery.

96
00:06:35,728 --> 00:06:36,979
Of course.

97
00:06:37,063 --> 00:06:40,191
You guys are welcome to stay here
for as long as you want.

98
00:06:40,733 --> 00:06:42,401
And it's also good for Mikoy,

99
00:06:42,485 --> 00:06:44,403
that he has someone to keep him company.

100
00:06:44,487 --> 00:06:47,824
Because his job still feels new to him.

101
00:06:47,907 --> 00:06:50,535
Oh, yes, he can definitely
handle all of that.

102
00:06:50,618 --> 00:06:52,829
And we fully support him.

103
00:06:53,329 --> 00:06:56,374
As long as he never gets involved
with those syndicates,

104
00:06:56,457 --> 00:06:58,876
the ones doing bad things.

105
00:06:59,627 --> 00:07:03,256
Oh my. You know what?
This one really overthinks!

106
00:07:03,339 --> 00:07:05,007
What are you even talking about?!

107
00:07:05,091 --> 00:07:07,552
Is this like Mafia?

108
00:07:07,635 --> 00:07:08,719
- Yakuza?
- I'm just--

109
00:07:08,803 --> 00:07:09,929
There's nothing like that
in the Philippines!

110
00:07:10,012 --> 00:07:12,056
I'm just making sure. You know me.

111
00:07:12,140 --> 00:07:14,434
When it comes
to illegal things, I'm allergic.

112
00:07:15,935 --> 00:07:19,147
Do you think our son
would do anything illegal?

113
00:07:19,230 --> 00:07:22,150
Our son is a good man, my love.

114
00:07:22,233 --> 00:07:23,985
You know, our Mikoy,

115
00:07:24,944 --> 00:07:27,947
he was a sacristan
throughout elementary school.

116
00:07:28,030 --> 00:07:29,532
He takes after his father.

117
00:07:32,326 --> 00:07:33,995
How was your day?

118
00:07:34,078 --> 00:07:36,456
Did you get to look around here in Manila?

119
00:07:36,539 --> 00:07:37,999
Did you enjoy it?

120
00:07:38,082 --> 00:07:42,336
No. We just delivered
some of our cake orders.

121
00:07:43,337 --> 00:07:44,297
Where to?

122
00:07:44,380 --> 00:07:46,132
To the office of Mikoy's friend.

123
00:07:46,215 --> 00:07:47,341
- Alex.
- Yes.

124
00:07:50,303 --> 00:07:52,680
Do you happen to know Alex?

125
00:07:52,763 --> 00:07:54,640
Oh my, I don't know that person.

126
00:07:54,724 --> 00:07:58,352
I was actually surprised
he knew someone here in Manila.

127
00:07:58,436 --> 00:08:00,021
Do you know that person?

128
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:03,024
Not really.

129
00:08:04,066 --> 00:08:07,403
I haven't met any friend
of Mikoy named Alex.

130
00:08:07,487 --> 00:08:11,282
The Alex I know
is the one grilling chicken.

131
00:08:12,825 --> 00:08:13,784
Exactly!

132
00:08:23,878 --> 00:08:25,630
Are you sure you’re okay?

133
00:08:27,882 --> 00:08:28,966
You know,

134
00:08:30,134 --> 00:08:31,761
I'm impressed with you.

135
00:08:31,844 --> 00:08:33,054
Yes.

136
00:08:33,137 --> 00:08:35,932
You survived
your first assassination attempt.

137
00:08:36,807 --> 00:08:38,726
It takes a lot of guts to do that.

138
00:08:40,436 --> 00:08:41,354
Wow!

139
00:08:41,437 --> 00:08:42,647
You know,

140
00:08:42,730 --> 00:08:45,942
I think that's the first nice thing
you've said about me.

141
00:08:46,901 --> 00:08:47,985
I like it.

142
00:08:48,069 --> 00:08:52,198
You know, that's one of the habits
of highly effective people.

143
00:08:52,281 --> 00:08:55,034
Like we should celebrate
everyone’s contribution,

144
00:08:55,117 --> 00:08:58,454
instead of competing with each other
just to get recognition.

145
00:09:03,292 --> 00:09:04,335
That's right!

146
00:09:04,418 --> 00:09:07,421
Like what Linny, Ming-ming,
and Tuck said, right?

147
00:09:17,932 --> 00:09:19,684
If I'm not mistaken,

148
00:09:19,767 --> 00:09:22,270
this is a very popular asset.

149
00:09:22,353 --> 00:09:25,731
Michael Mikoy D. Pinagpala.

150
00:09:26,524 --> 00:09:27,692
Yes, sir!

151
00:09:27,775 --> 00:09:28,943
Mikoy Pinagpala

152
00:09:29,026 --> 00:09:30,653
at your service.

153
00:09:30,736 --> 00:09:33,197
Agent Director Norberto Ruiz.

154
00:09:33,281 --> 00:09:34,657
Have a seat.

155
00:09:54,677 --> 00:09:58,472
<i>The subscriber cannot be reached.</i>
<i>Please try again later.</i>

156
00:09:59,056 --> 00:10:01,517
I tried calling him,
but he can't be reached.

157
00:10:02,184 --> 00:10:05,021
The office said
he stopped by the warehouse.

158
00:10:06,188 --> 00:10:08,858
Maybe there's no signal in that area.

159
00:10:08,941 --> 00:10:11,110
Or maybe he's on his way home.

160
00:10:11,694 --> 00:10:12,987
Let's wait a little longer.

161
00:10:14,614 --> 00:10:16,407
Honey, the food's getting cold.

162
00:10:16,490 --> 00:10:17,575
- Come on, Chiara.
- You’re right.

163
00:10:17,658 --> 00:10:18,826
Come, eat now.

164
00:10:18,909 --> 00:10:21,287
Or we might end up starving.

165
00:10:21,370 --> 00:10:23,039
Oh dear, we might get ulcers.

166
00:10:23,122 --> 00:10:24,123
- Come on, eat now.
- Right.

167
00:10:24,206 --> 00:10:25,750
- Come on.
- Quick.

168
00:10:25,833 --> 00:10:27,960
There you go! Let's give you two servings!

169
00:10:28,044 --> 00:10:30,046
- I want you to eat a lot.
- That's enough for me.

170
00:10:31,047 --> 00:10:32,506
No dieting!

171
00:10:33,257 --> 00:10:34,759
- Well then, now.
- There

172
00:10:34,842 --> 00:10:36,218
You’re next, my love.

173
00:10:36,302 --> 00:10:38,304
- Okay, sure.
- Of course, I won't forget you.

174
00:10:38,387 --> 00:10:40,139
- All right.
- This one's for you.

175
00:10:42,058 --> 00:10:42,892
Is it good?

176
00:10:43,434 --> 00:10:44,769
Delicious! It’s fried.

177
00:10:45,436 --> 00:10:46,812
Here. Have this, too.

178
00:10:48,481 --> 00:10:49,523
Wait.

179
00:10:52,401 --> 00:10:54,070
- So crispy!
- Right?

180
00:10:54,153 --> 00:10:56,530
- So good!
- It's fried well!

181
00:10:57,948 --> 00:10:58,783
One more.

182
00:10:59,784 --> 00:11:01,077
It’s your turn.

183
00:11:01,577 --> 00:11:02,703
How embarassing for you.

184
00:11:04,497 --> 00:11:05,539
Here.

185
00:11:13,422 --> 00:11:15,883
The one who attacked you
was Jepoy's brother.

186
00:11:17,843 --> 00:11:19,345
And according to him,

187
00:11:19,428 --> 00:11:21,514
he was just avenging his brother.

188
00:11:22,264 --> 00:11:23,099
Wait a second.

189
00:11:23,182 --> 00:11:25,226
Who exactly is this Jepoy?

190
00:11:25,810 --> 00:11:27,353
He used to be Viktor's right-hand man.

191
00:11:28,354 --> 00:11:30,815
And when Viktor and Donabel
were still in Prague,

192
00:11:30,898 --> 00:11:33,484
he was running
the operations in the Philippines.

193
00:11:33,567 --> 00:11:36,028
But when you arrived,

194
00:11:37,029 --> 00:11:38,989
we found him dead in his apartment.

195
00:11:40,032 --> 00:11:42,118
So he died because of me?

196
00:11:43,452 --> 00:11:44,495
Not necessarily.

197
00:11:45,079 --> 00:11:48,374
But we really believe that he
was threatened by your arrival.

198
00:11:49,458 --> 00:11:51,085
Especially now that

199
00:11:51,794 --> 00:11:55,214
Viktor Valtrovi's only daughter
is deeply in love with you.

200
00:12:03,180 --> 00:12:04,390
How did you know about this?

201
00:12:04,473 --> 00:12:06,434
Kian was spying on him.

202
00:12:06,517 --> 00:12:07,893
Unfortunately,

203
00:12:07,977 --> 00:12:09,979
Kian paid a dear price.

204
00:12:18,654 --> 00:12:20,197
And that's not all.

205
00:12:23,284 --> 00:12:25,411
from a police substation in Bulacan.

206
00:12:35,296 --> 00:12:37,715
From the pattern that we see here, Mikoy,

207
00:12:37,798 --> 00:12:39,341
there's only one thing we can say.

208
00:12:41,010 --> 00:12:43,179
Looks like Viktor is cleaning up.

209
00:12:44,013 --> 00:12:45,306
Cleaning up what?

210
00:12:46,182 --> 00:12:48,851
He's already cleaning out his enemies.

211
00:12:55,733 --> 00:12:56,567
It seems that

212
00:12:57,818 --> 00:12:59,737
he's setting you up

213
00:13:00,779 --> 00:13:03,449
to become the Moraviano <i>principale.</i>

214
00:13:05,576 --> 00:13:08,954
You will become the leader
of the entire syndicate.

215
00:13:35,147 --> 00:13:37,066
If it weren't for you,

216
00:13:37,149 --> 00:13:39,151
my brother would still be alive today!

217
00:13:39,944 --> 00:13:42,029
<i>I'll kill you first,</i>

218
00:13:42,112 --> 00:13:43,822
<i>to send a message to Viktor!</i>

219
00:13:58,337 --> 00:13:59,755
You’re not allowed here, right?

220
00:14:00,756 --> 00:14:02,383
Isn't this for men?

221
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:06,178
Our office bathrooms are gender-neutral.

222
00:14:09,848 --> 00:14:11,392
Is there a problem?

223
00:14:13,269 --> 00:14:15,062
I guess I'm just feeling guilty.

224
00:14:17,940 --> 00:14:20,484
Some people are dying because of me.

225
00:14:20,985 --> 00:14:22,862
Are you really still blaming yourself?

226
00:14:22,945 --> 00:14:24,655
But it's true, isn't it?

227
00:14:24,738 --> 00:14:27,199
What about Jepoy and his companion?

228
00:14:31,829 --> 00:14:34,748
If it weren't for me,
maybe they'd still be alive.

229
00:14:36,208 --> 00:14:39,211
Do you think if you hadn't met Chiara,

230
00:14:39,295 --> 00:14:42,339
no one else would die
and fall victim to the Moravianos?

231
00:14:43,090 --> 00:14:44,675
What you've seen is only a glimpse

232
00:14:44,758 --> 00:14:47,303
of Viktor and his wife’s wickedness.

233
00:14:49,096 --> 00:14:50,055
As time goes by,

234
00:14:50,139 --> 00:14:53,809
their influence grows bigger
and their forces grow stronger.

235
00:14:55,185 --> 00:14:59,273
Kian and Jepoy are not
their first and last victims.

236
00:14:59,773 --> 00:15:01,859
A lot of people
will get dragged into this.

237
00:15:01,942 --> 00:15:04,987
More lives will be ruined by them.

238
00:15:05,070 --> 00:15:06,947
So I'll admit it, Mikoy.

239
00:15:09,325 --> 00:15:10,993
I need you.

240
00:15:15,497 --> 00:15:16,707
I know

241
00:15:17,750 --> 00:15:19,793
I am putting you in a rough spot.

242
00:15:20,502 --> 00:15:22,296
I’m putting you in a dangerous situation.

243
00:15:23,839 --> 00:15:26,467
But if you're not around,

244
00:15:27,676 --> 00:15:30,596
we don't know how we can
bring down the Moravianos.

245
00:15:31,347 --> 00:15:34,350
And we won't be able
to give justice to their victims, either.

246
00:15:35,851 --> 00:15:37,561
And the most painful part of all,

247
00:15:38,479 --> 00:15:41,482
more people will be dragged
into their evil deeds.

248
00:16:07,132 --> 00:16:09,426
For God's sake, holy heavens!

249
00:16:12,930 --> 00:16:14,932
You're here again?

250
00:16:46,964 --> 00:16:47,840
What now, Bok?

251
00:16:48,507 --> 00:16:49,341
How is it?

252
00:16:49,425 --> 00:16:50,676
Is he in or out?

253
00:16:53,012 --> 00:16:55,848
He hasn't said anything yet,
but I think he is in.

254
00:16:55,931 --> 00:16:58,183
How can you say that?

255
00:16:58,267 --> 00:16:59,643
You know,

256
00:16:59,727 --> 00:17:02,271
after everything that person
has been through,

257
00:17:02,354 --> 00:17:04,523
I think he'll start having
second thoughts.

258
00:17:04,606 --> 00:17:07,484
And it will be hard to get him
to cooperate with us.

259
00:17:09,403 --> 00:17:10,571
I don't think so.

260
00:17:12,698 --> 00:17:14,575
You know that's your problem?

261
00:17:15,659 --> 00:17:17,453
You always underestimate him.

262
00:17:18,245 --> 00:17:19,538
But what you don't know

263
00:17:19,621 --> 00:17:22,041
is that this person has a big heart.

264
00:17:23,417 --> 00:17:25,169
<i>Sometimes it’s not obvious,</i>

265
00:17:25,669 --> 00:17:29,339
<i>but he’s the kind of person</i>
<i>who does things</i>

266
00:17:29,423 --> 00:17:31,884
<i>not because it’s hard or easy,</i>

267
00:17:33,052 --> 00:17:34,928
<i>but because it’s the right thing to do.</i>

268
00:17:35,012 --> 00:17:36,805
- There he is!
- Hurry up!

269
00:17:36,889 --> 00:17:39,099
Sir, can we ask for a Christmas gift?

270
00:17:39,183 --> 00:17:40,059
A Christmas gift?

271
00:17:40,142 --> 00:17:41,226
Wait.

272
00:17:41,310 --> 00:17:42,561
Christmas is still far away.

273
00:17:42,644 --> 00:17:44,396
But didn’t they say

274
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:47,566
we should live like
every day is Christmas?

275
00:17:47,649 --> 00:17:48,484
So,

276
00:17:48,567 --> 00:17:51,111
even if it's not Christmas yet,
we're already caroling.

277
00:17:54,156 --> 00:17:56,241
- You do have a point.
- See?

278
00:17:56,325 --> 00:17:58,786
- All right! Go for it!
- All right!

279
00:17:58,869 --> 00:18:00,704
- There! That’s a lot of money!
- Here.

280
00:18:00,788 --> 00:18:02,915
Okay. One, two, three!

281
00:18:02,998 --> 00:18:05,375
<i>Christmas has come…</i>

282
00:18:09,630 --> 00:18:12,466
<i>Because he’s the type of person</i>
<i>who will make the sacrifice.</i>

283
00:18:12,549 --> 00:18:14,051
<i>He’s the type of person</i>

284
00:18:14,134 --> 00:18:16,887
<i>who can sacrifice everything</i>
<i>for the person he loves.</i>

285
00:19:54,401 --> 00:19:55,360
- Hey.
- Mikoy.

286
00:19:56,778 --> 00:19:58,197
Have you been here long?

287
00:20:01,325 --> 00:20:02,492
Have you eaten yet?

288
00:20:03,285 --> 00:20:04,578
I'll warm up some food for you.

289
00:20:04,661 --> 00:20:06,622
No need. I’m not hungry.

290
00:20:06,705 --> 00:20:07,581
It's okay.

291
00:20:11,585 --> 00:20:12,419
I'm okay.

292
00:20:13,545 --> 00:20:14,630
Thank you.

293
00:20:19,384 --> 00:20:21,094
I'm not hungry.

294
00:20:21,678 --> 00:20:23,180
They…

295
00:20:23,263 --> 00:20:27,392
Mom and Dad are already in the guest room.

296
00:20:27,476 --> 00:20:29,311
They said it's their loving time.

297
00:20:34,066 --> 00:20:35,275
Sorry.

298
00:20:35,359 --> 00:20:36,944
Looks like those two traumatized you.

299
00:20:45,661 --> 00:20:48,580
Why did you come home late?

300
00:20:53,710 --> 00:20:56,922
I just had a lot of things
to fix at the office.

301
00:20:59,591 --> 00:21:01,176
There are just so many problems there.

302
00:21:02,511 --> 00:21:03,553
Well…

303
00:21:04,304 --> 00:21:06,139
Don't spread yourself too thin.

304
00:21:06,932 --> 00:21:10,352
You might end up neglecting yourself.

305
00:21:15,023 --> 00:21:16,316
That's okay.

306
00:21:16,942 --> 00:21:18,402
It's a small thing.

307
00:21:18,902 --> 00:21:22,864
At least I can somehow repay
the trust your daddy gave me.

308
00:21:25,325 --> 00:21:26,910
You know,

309
00:21:29,079 --> 00:21:31,540
I'm so lucky that I met you.

310
00:21:53,645 --> 00:21:54,938
Why?

311
00:21:58,900 --> 00:22:00,193
What? Why?

312
00:22:00,777 --> 00:22:02,779
I haven't brushed my teeth yet!

313
00:22:03,363 --> 00:22:05,615
- What?
- Not yet.

314
00:22:06,700 --> 00:22:08,660
Stop being so fussy!

315
00:22:08,744 --> 00:22:10,370
- Come on!
- I don’t like!

316
00:22:12,164 --> 00:22:13,457
That’s okay!

317
00:22:21,673 --> 00:22:23,717
Why don't you want to kiss me?

318
00:22:23,800 --> 00:22:25,510
Just kiss me already!

319
00:22:26,261 --> 00:22:27,304
Wait a second!

320
00:22:28,013 --> 00:22:28,847
Do you really want to?

321
00:22:30,140 --> 00:22:31,099
Do you want to?

322
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:32,893
Maybe not anymore.

323
00:22:32,976 --> 00:22:34,519
- Do you want to?
- I’m good now.

324
00:22:37,022 --> 00:22:38,231
Come here!

325
00:22:42,569 --> 00:22:44,446
It actually smells! It smells!

326
00:22:44,529 --> 00:22:46,031
I’m not smelly!

327
00:22:46,114 --> 00:22:47,783
You are smelly!

328
00:22:49,201 --> 00:22:50,577
Put me down! One!

329
00:22:52,162 --> 00:22:53,497
No!

330
00:22:56,792 --> 00:22:59,711
Oh, really, you like me, huh?

331
00:23:03,840 --> 00:23:05,509
No, Mikoy.

332
00:23:05,592 --> 00:23:07,177
Don't fall for her.

333
00:23:07,928 --> 00:23:10,263
You shouldn't trust her so easily.

334
00:23:11,681 --> 00:23:12,557
Bok.

335
00:23:14,017 --> 00:23:15,143
Are you busy?

336
00:23:16,186 --> 00:23:18,313
Not really. I just finished a report.

337
00:23:19,397 --> 00:23:20,774
Oh, okay.

338
00:23:23,318 --> 00:23:24,319
Beer.

339
00:23:31,952 --> 00:23:32,786
Cheers!

340
00:23:33,703 --> 00:23:34,955
Come on, smile.

341
00:23:50,345 --> 00:23:53,181
<i>He’ll really just do whatever he’s told.</i>

342
00:23:54,141 --> 00:23:55,392
<i>Gosh!</i>

343
00:24:10,031 --> 00:24:11,867
- Cheers, Bok!
- Cheers!

344
00:24:17,789 --> 00:24:19,332
Hey, hey!

345
00:24:19,416 --> 00:24:20,750
Take it slow!

346
00:24:21,835 --> 00:24:22,878
One more.

347
00:24:25,172 --> 00:24:26,089
You’re crazy.

348
00:24:28,967 --> 00:24:30,427
Do you feel guilty?

349
00:24:31,636 --> 00:24:32,762
Guilty about what?

350
00:24:33,263 --> 00:24:34,764
About what we’re doing to Mikoy.

351
00:24:39,728 --> 00:24:41,479
As they say,

352
00:24:42,981 --> 00:24:44,316
ignorance is bliss.

353
00:24:45,775 --> 00:24:49,321
Because if we hadn’t
recruited Mikoy for our mission,

354
00:24:50,739 --> 00:24:53,950
he’s probably just happy now with Chiara.

355
00:24:54,034 --> 00:24:58,955
He’s just thinking about how
they’ll always love each other, right?

356
00:24:59,039 --> 00:25:00,916
Is that real happiness?

357
00:25:02,876 --> 00:25:04,669
Can you really be happy with someone,

358
00:25:04,753 --> 00:25:07,923
even if you don’t know the truth
about her and her family?

359
00:25:09,299 --> 00:25:11,509
Well, you have a point there.

360
00:25:13,303 --> 00:25:16,348
Maybe what I’m afraid of
is that he ends up like us, Bok.

361
00:25:17,015 --> 00:25:19,267
What do you mean?
We’re fine, Bok, aren’t we?

362
00:25:20,977 --> 00:25:22,854
Are we really okay?

363
00:25:24,522 --> 00:25:26,858
With everything we’ve been through,
do you think

364
00:25:27,567 --> 00:25:29,194
we can still trust people?

365
00:25:29,277 --> 00:25:31,988
Do you think we can still love?

366
00:25:32,906 --> 00:25:34,532
We still can, Bok.

367
00:25:35,533 --> 00:25:37,118
You just have to trust.

368
00:25:37,619 --> 00:25:40,789
I know we see the darkness of humanity,

369
00:25:40,872 --> 00:25:43,792
but we still deserve to be loved

370
00:25:43,875 --> 00:25:46,211
and to love others.

371
00:25:48,463 --> 00:25:50,423
I hope you’re right, Bok.

372
00:25:51,466 --> 00:25:52,509
And you?

373
00:25:54,010 --> 00:25:55,303
You’re not hard to love.

374
00:25:56,680 --> 00:25:58,473
How can you say that?

375
00:25:59,557 --> 00:26:01,017
Just a little makeover.

376
00:26:04,938 --> 00:26:05,981
Crazy!

377
00:26:07,399 --> 00:26:09,192
Anyway, cheers!

378
00:26:10,527 --> 00:26:12,279
Cheers to us!

379
00:26:12,362 --> 00:26:15,699
And hoping that love will find us, Bok.

380
00:26:16,199 --> 00:26:17,284
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

381
00:26:31,172 --> 00:26:34,634
CALLING
MIKOY

382
00:26:40,473 --> 00:26:41,558
Yes, Mikoy?

383
00:26:51,901 --> 00:26:53,945
I want to fully commit to this mission.

384
00:26:58,325 --> 00:27:01,745
I’m ready to help
you bring down the Moravianos.

385
00:27:25,226 --> 00:27:26,644
<i>If not me, then who?</i>

386
00:27:26,728 --> 00:27:28,605
<i>If not now, then when?</i>

387
00:27:29,773 --> 00:27:31,149
<i>Maybe</i>

388
00:27:31,232 --> 00:27:34,027
<i>heaven is giving me</i>
<i>a chance to do what is right.</i>

389
00:27:37,197 --> 00:27:39,949
You might be getting influenced by him.

390
00:27:41,701 --> 00:27:44,829
Do you think she knows anything
about what her parents are doing?
